usbMib.name: usbMib
usbMib.contactinfo: Benjamin Dolnik Postal: 3Com Corporation 3800 Golf Road Rolling Meadows, IL 60008 USA Phone: +1 847 262 2098 E-mail: benjamin-dolnik@3com.com
usbMib.description: The MIB module to describe the USB interface.

usbNumber.name: usbNumber
usbNumber.description: The number of ports regardless of their current state in the usb general port table

usbPortTable.name: usbPortTable
usbPortTable.description: A list of port entries. The number of entries is given by the value usbNumber.

usbPortEntry.name: usbPortEntry
usbPortEntry.description: Status and parameter values for the USB port.

usbPortIndex.name: usbPortIndex
usbPortIndex.description: The unique identifier of the USB port hardware. By convention and if possible, hardware port numbers map directly to external connectors.

usbPortType.name: usbPortType
usbPortType.description: The type of the USB port

usbPortRate.name: usbPortRate
usbPortRate.description: The USB port rate that could be low-speed(1) for 1.5 Mbps, full-speed(2) for 12Mbps or high-speed(3) for USB 2.0

usbDeviceTable.name: usbDeviceTable
usbDeviceTable.description: A list of USB device ports. Usually the device has only one USB device port

usbDeviceEntry.name: usbDeviceEntry
usbDeviceEntry.description: Status and parameter values for the USB device port.

usbDeviceIndex.name: usbDeviceIndex
usbDeviceIndex.description: The index is identical to usbPortIndex for the correspondent USB port

usbDevicePower.name: usbDevicePower
usbDevicePower.description: the way USB device port is powered

usbDeviceVendorID.name: usbDeviceVendorID
usbDeviceVendorID.description: The USB device port vendor HEX-formatted string as it is provided to the USB host by the USB device

usbDeviceProductID.name: usbDeviceProductID
usbDeviceProductID.description: The product ID HEX-formatted string as it is provided to the USB host by the USB device

usbDeviceNumberConfigurations.name: usbDeviceNumberConfigurations
usbDeviceNumberConfigurations.description: The total number of configurations the USB port supports. Device port should support at least one configuration

usbDeviceActiveClass.name: usbDeviceActiveClass
usbDeviceActiveClass.description: This object returns USB Device Class type of the active configuration

usbDeviceStatus.name: usbDeviceStatus
usbDeviceStatus.description: Current status of the USB device state machine

usbDeviceEnumCounter.name: usbDeviceEnumCounter
usbDeviceEnumCounter.description: Total number reconnections (enumerations) since device is operational

usbDeviceRemoteWakeup.name: usbDeviceRemoteWakeup
usbDeviceRemoteWakeup.description: If set to true(1), the device supports Remote Wakeup function. If set to false(2), the device doesn't support it

usbDeviceRemoteWakeupOn.name: usbDeviceRemoteWakeupOn
usbDeviceRemoteWakeupOn.description: If set to true(1), the remote wakeup function is activated by the host. If set to false(2), remote wakeup function is not active.

usbCDCTable.name: usbCDCTable
usbCDCTable.description: A list of Communication Device Class (CDC) interfaces supported by the USB device. It could be more then one CDC interface for the device that expose more then one interface to the network

usbCDCEntry.name: usbCDCEntry
usbCDCEntry.description: Status and parameter values for CDC device

usbCDCIndex.name: usbCDCIndex
usbCDCIndex.description: The index is identical to usbPortIndex for the correspondent USB port

usbCDCIfIndex.name: usbCDCIfIndex
usbCDCIfIndex.description: The variable uniquely identifies the interface index which this CDC device is representing

usbCDCSubclass.name: usbCDCSubclass
usbCDCSubclass.reference: USB Class definitions for Communication Devices ver 1.1, p.28
usbCDCSubclass.description: Subclass used in data transfer in Communication Device Class

usbCDCVersion.name: usbCDCVersion
usbCDCVersion.description: String that describes the version of Communication Device Class in HEX format (Major, Minor)

usbCDCDataTransferType.name: usbCDCDataTransferType
usbCDCDataTransferType.description: Type of data transfer for Data Class Interface used by the Communication Device. Isochronious mode is used for synchronous(1) and bulk transfer mode is used for asynchronous(2)

usbCDCDataEndpoints.name: usbCDCDataEndpoints
usbCDCDataEndpoints.description: Number of the data endpoints (IN and OUT) used by the Communication Device. If the networking device is in default interface setting, there are are no data endpoints and no traffic is exchanged. Under the normal operation there should be 2 Data Endpoints (one IN and one OUT) for the networking device. For the multichannel model this number could be larger then 2

usbCDCStalls.name: usbCDCStalls
usbCDCStalls.description: Total number of times USB Data interface recovered from stall since re-initialization and while the port state was 'up' or 'test'.

usbCDCEtherTable.name: usbCDCEtherTable
usbCDCEtherTable.description: A list of Communication Device Class (CDC) USB devices that support Ethernet Networking Control Model.

usbCDCEtherEntry.name: usbCDCEtherEntry
usbCDCEtherEntry.description: Status and parameter values for CDC devices that support Ethernet Networking Control Model

usbCDCEtherIndex.name: usbCDCEtherIndex
usbCDCEtherIndex.description: The index is identical to usbPortIndex for the correspondent USB port

usbCDCEtherIfIndex.name: usbCDCEtherIfIndex
usbCDCEtherIfIndex.description: The variable uniquely identifies the interface index to which this CDC device is connected

usbCDCEtherMacAddress.name: usbCDCEtherMacAddress
usbCDCEtherMacAddress.description: The 48bit MAC address that is provided by USB CDC device to the host. This address will be used as the source address of Ethernet frames sent by the host over the particular CDC interface.

usbCDCEtherPacketFilter.name: usbCDCEtherPacketFilter
usbCDCEtherPacketFilter.reference: USB Class definitions for Communication Devices ver 1.1, p.66 Table 62
usbCDCEtherPacketFilter.description: Bitmap indicates the host requirements to the USB device to perform Ethernet packet filtering of the particular type frames directed to the host

usbCDCEtherDataStatisticsCapabilities.name: usbCDCEtherDataStatisticsCapabilities
usbCDCEtherDataStatisticsCapabilities.reference: USB Class definitions for Communication Devices ver 1.1, p.46 Table 42
usbCDCEtherDataStatisticsCapabilities.description: Bitmap indicates the ability to collect Ethernet statistics of different types as it provided in Ethernet Networking Functional Descriptor. If the Particular bit is set, the device could provide the corresponding statistics counter to the host

usbCDCEtherDataCheckErrs.name: usbCDCEtherDataCheckErrs
usbCDCEtherDataCheckErrs.description: Total number of frames with an invalid frame check sequence, input from the USB Data interface since system re-initialization and while the port state was 'up' or 'test'.

usbCDCEtherXmtAddressTable.name: usbCDCEtherXmtAddressTable
usbCDCEtherXmtAddressTable.description: This table contains an entry for each multicast address for which the system will transmit packets/frames on a particular USB interface.

usbCDCEtherXmtAddressEntry.name: usbCDCEtherXmtAddressEntry
usbCDCEtherXmtAddressEntry.description: A list of objects identifying an address for which the system will send packets/frames on the particular USB interface identified by the index values usbCDCIndex and ifIndex.

ifCDCEtherXmtAddress.name: ifCDCEtherXmtAddress
ifCDCEtherXmtAddress.description: An address for which the system will will send packets/frames on the particular USB interface. The address only could be set by the host by using the command for USB interface.

usbMibBasicCompliance.name: usbMibBasicCompliance
usbMibBasicCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement USB MIB

usbMibBasicGroup.name: usbMibBasicGroup
usbMibBasicGroup.description: Group of objects that are mandatory to support by device implementing this MIB

usbMibCDCGroup.name: usbMibCDCGroup
usbMibCDCGroup.description: This group is implemented only in devices having at least one CDC interface

usbMibCDCEtherGroup.name: usbMibCDCEtherGroup
usbMibCDCEtherGroup.description: This group is implemented only in devices having at least one CDC interface that uses Ethernet Networking Control Model or remote NDIS

usbCDCEtherXmtAddressGroup.name: usbCDCEtherXmtAddressGroup
usbCDCEtherXmtAddressGroup.description: This group is implemented only for USB CDC interfaces that have transmit multicast filtering capabilities.
